## 5. Step 3: Model Training (scripts/)

### 5.1 Execution Structure

```
run_ktemp.sh
  └─▶ ktemp.py
        └─▶ ../Model/KTEMPCAST.py
        └─▶ ../utils/
```

### 5.2 Case Configuration

Case selection is controlled by the value of `w` at **line 215 of `Model/KTEMPCAST.py`**:

- **GL case** (no regional branch): `w = 0` → `p_final = pg`
- **NA case:** set `w` to learned gate weight (non-zero); configure regional crop to NA coordinates
- **EA case:** same as NA but set regional crop coordinates to EA region

Regional branch coordinates:
- NA: latitude 0–60°N, longitude 80°W–0°
- EA: latitude 0–50°N, longitude 90–150°E

### 5.3 Meta-learning Configuration (Table 1 Summary)

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Training period | 1950–2004 (55 years) |
| Test period | 2005–2024 (20 years) |
| Support set | 5 years/episode (stratified sampling from 20-year rolling pool) |
| Query set | 15 years/episode (random from full training period) |
| Inner-loop updates | 3 gradient steps (head_g, head_r, gate_fc1, gate_fc2 only) |
| Outer-loop optimizer | Adam, lr 0.002 → 0.001 (300 iterations) |
| Ensemble members | 30 (different random seeds) |
| Loss function | MSE + α·ExLoss (α = 100/81) |

### 5.4 Training Execution

```bash
cd scripts/

# GL case (verify w=0 at line 215 of KTEMPCAST.py)
bash run_ktemp.sh

# NA case (activate w, set NA region)
bash run_ktemp.sh

# Background execution (prevent disconnection)
nohup bash run_ktemp.sh > log_gl.out 2>&1 &
echo $!   # Check PID (to terminate: kill <PID>)
```

