## 6. Step 4: Verification and Visualization (src/)

### 6.1 Time-series Prediction Plot — `drawgl.py`

Plots K-TempCast predictions vs. ERA5 vs. GloSea6 time series (Figure 2 format).

- GL case: run as is
- NA/EA case: change the `name` variable inside the script to `'NA'` or `'EA'`

```bash
cd src/
python drawgl.py
```

### 6.2 Tercile Performance Diagram — `trnmax_new.py`

Visualizes Cold/Normal/Warm tercile prediction performance as a Performance Diagram (POD vs SR with CSI contours; Figures 3, 4, 5 format).

```bash
python trnmax_new.py
```

### 6.3 GloSea6 Reference File Format

GloSea6 result files (`jun/jul/aug.ano.2005-2024.1-9.txt`) contain ensemble-mean anomalies (K) for each year based on 1st and 9th initialization dates, stored in chronological order. See `src/README.txt` for detailed format.

